This paper deals with a control problem involving multiple agents and shared resources, which is a classic problem in multi-agent systems (MAS) and game theory (GT). The paper proposes a new algorithm with convergence and optimality guarantees, which is a typical topic in machine learning (ML) and optimization (OPT). The paper also mentions the application of the problem in smart cities, which is related to systems and control (SY) and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.MA, followed by cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.SY, and cs.AI.
